.TH "tb_xdomain_enable_paths" 9 "tb_xdomain_enable_paths" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tb_xdomain_enable_paths \- Enable DMA paths for XDomain connection
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" tb_xdomain_enable_paths
.BI "(struct tb_xdomain *xd "  ","
.BI "u16 transmit_path "  ","
.BI "u16 transmit_ring "  ","
.BI "u16 receive_path "  ","
.BI "u16 receive_ring "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "xd" 12
XDomain connection
.IP "transmit_path" 12
HopID of the transmit path the other end is using to
send packets
.IP "transmit_ring" 12
DMA ring used to receive packets from the other end
.IP "receive_path" 12
HopID of the receive path the other end is using to
receive packets
.IP "receive_ring" 12
DMA ring used to send packets to the other end
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The function enables DMA paths accordingly so that after successful
return the caller can send and receive packets using high-speed DMA
path.
.SH "RETURN"
0 in case of success and negative errno in case of error
